@startuml CouponSystem_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Coupon System on Shopping Cart (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Cart has Rs 2000 of items. User applies 'FLAT200' coupon. System validates, checks eligibility, calculates discount, applies. Total: Rs 1800."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class CouponService <<Facade>> {
    - couponRepository : CouponRepository
    - validationChain : CouponValidator
    - discountEngine : DiscountEngine
    --
    + applyCoupon(cart, couponCode) : DiscountResult
    + removeCoupon(cart) : void
    + validateCoupon(cart, couponCode) : ValidationResult
    + getAvailableCoupons(cart) : List<Coupon>
    + createCoupon(coupon) : Coupon
    + deactivateCoupon(couponId) : void
}

note top of CouponService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "User has a cart with items. Types coupon
    code 'FLAT200'. Client calls
    applyCoupon(cart, 'FLAT200')."

    "CouponService is the **Facade** — coordinates:
    1. Look up coupon from repository
    2. Validate via validation chain
    3. Calculate discount via engine
    4. Apply to cart and return result."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CART + PRODUCT MODELS
' ====================================================================
class Cart {
    - cartId : String
    - userId : String
    - items : List<CartItem>
    - appliedCoupon : Coupon
    - discountAmount : double
    --
    + addItem(product, qty) : void
    + removeItem(productId) : void
    + getSubtotal() : double
    + getTotal() : double
    + getItems() : List<CartItem>
    + applyCoupon(coupon, discount) : void
    + removeCoupon() : void
    + getAppliedCoupon() : Coupon
    + getItemsByCategory(cat) : List<CartItem>
}

class CartItem {
    - product : Product
    - quantity : int
    --
    + getSubtotal() : double
    + getProduct() : Product
    + getQuantity() : int
}

class Product {
    - productId : String
    - name : String
    - price : double
    - category : ProductCategory
    - brand : String
    - sellerId : String
    --
    + getPrice() : double
    + getCategory() : ProductCategory
    + getBrand() : String
}

enum ProductCategory {
    ELECTRONICS
    CLOTHING
    GROCERY
    BOOKS
    BEAUTY
    HOME
}

note top of Cart #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - The shopping cart.**
    "**Cart** has items, a subtotal, and optionally
    an applied coupon with calculated discount.
    getTotal() = getSubtotal() - discountAmount."

    "**CartItem** = Product + quantity.
    **Product** has price, category, brand.
    Category and brand matter because coupons
    can target specific categories/brands."
end note

Cart *-- CartItem : contains >
CartItem --> Product : for >
Product --> ProductCategory
CouponService --> Cart : applies to >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: COUPON MODEL
' ====================================================================
class Coupon {
    - couponId : String
    - code : String
    - description : String
    - discountType : DiscountType
    - discountValue : double
    - maxDiscount : double
    - minCartValue : double
    - applicableCategories : Set<ProductCategory>
    - applicableBrands : Set<String>
    - applicableProducts : Set<String>
    - startDate : LocalDate
    - endDate : LocalDate
    - maxUsageTotal : int
    - maxUsagePerUser : int
    - currentUsageCount : int
    - isActive : bool
    - isStackable : bool
    --
    + isValid() : bool
    + isExpired() : bool
    + isUsageLimitReached() : bool
    + appliesToCategory(cat) : bool
    + appliesToBrand(brand) : bool
    + isUniversal() : bool
}

enum DiscountType {
    FLAT_AMOUNT
    PERCENTAGE
    BUY_X_GET_Y
    FREE_SHIPPING
    CASHBACK
}

class CouponRepository {
    - coupons : Map<String, Coupon>
    - codeIndex : Map<String, Coupon>
    --
    + findByCode(code) : Coupon
    + findById(couponId) : Coupon
    + save(coupon) : void
    + getActiveCoupons() : List<Coupon>
    + incrementUsage(couponId) : void
}

note top of Coupon #FFCDD2
    **STEP 3 - The coupon.**
    "**Coupon** is the richest model in the system:
    - discountType: FLAT_AMOUNT / PERCENTAGE /
      BUY_X_GET_Y / FREE_SHIPPING / CASHBACK
    - discountValue: Rs 200 or 15%
    - maxDiscount: cap at Rs 500 (for percentage)
    - minCartValue: 'min order Rs 999'
    - applicableCategories: only ELECTRONICS
    - applicableBrands: only 'Nike'
    - startDate/endDate: validity window
    - maxUsageTotal: 1000 total uses
    - maxUsagePerUser: 1 per user
    - isStackable: can combine with other coupons?"

    "**isUniversal()**: no category/brand/product
    restriction — applies to entire cart."
end note

Coupon --> DiscountType
CouponRepository o--> Coupon : stores >
CouponService --> CouponRepository


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: VALIDATION — Chain of Responsibility (KEY)
' ====================================================================
abstract class CouponValidator <<Handler>> {
    # nextValidator : CouponValidator
    --
    + setNext(validator) : CouponValidator
    + {abstract} validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class ExpiryValidator {
    + validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class MinCartValueValidator {
    + validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class UsageLimitValidator {
    - usageStore : Map<String, Map<String, Integer>>
    --
    + validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class CategoryValidator {
    + validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class StackabilityValidator {
    + validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class ActiveStatusValidator {
    + validate(cart, coupon) : ValidationResult
}

class ValidationResult {
    - valid : bool
    - errorMessage : String
    - errorCode : String
}

note top of CouponValidator #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - Validate the coupon. (KEY STEP)**
    "User enters 'FLAT200'. Is it valid for this cart?
    **Chain of Responsibility** — validators run
    in sequence. If any fails, reject immediately."

    "1. **ActiveStatusValidator**: is coupon active?
    2. **ExpiryValidator**: is it within date range?
    3. **MinCartValueValidator**: cart >= Rs 999?
    4. **UsageLimitValidator**: user hasn't exceeded
       per-user limit? Total uses not exceeded?
    5. **CategoryValidator**: does cart contain items
       from applicable categories/brands?
    6. **StackabilityValidator**: if cart already has
       a coupon, is this one stackable?"

    "Each validator checks one condition and passes
    to next. Add FirstTimeUserValidator? Insert
    in chain. Nothing else changes."
    **Pattern: Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP**
end note

CouponValidator <|-- ExpiryValidator
CouponValidator <|-- MinCartValueValidator
CouponValidator <|-- UsageLimitValidator
CouponValidator <|-- CategoryValidator
CouponValidator <|-- StackabilityValidator
CouponValidator <|-- ActiveStatusValidator
CouponValidator o--> CouponValidator : next >
CouponValidator --> ValidationResult : returns >
CouponService --> CouponValidator : validates via >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: DISCOUNT CALCULATION — Strategy Pattern (KEY)
' ====================================================================
class DiscountEngine {
    - strategies : Map<DiscountType, DiscountStrategy>
    --
    + calculateDiscount(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
    + registerStrategy(type, strategy) : void
}

interface DiscountStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class FlatAmountDiscount {
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class PercentageDiscount {
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class BuyXGetYDiscount {
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class FreeShippingDiscount {
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class CashbackDiscount {
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class DiscountResult {
    - success : bool
    - discountAmount : double
    - discountedItems : Map<String, Double>
    - message : String
    - originalTotal : double
    - finalTotal : double
    --
    + getSavingsPercent() : double
}

note top of DiscountStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Calculate the discount. (KEY STEP)**
    "Coupon validated. Now how much discount?"

    "**Strategy Pattern** — each discount type
    has its own calculation logic."

    "**FlatAmountDiscount**: 'FLAT200' -> Rs 200 off.
    If category-specific: only discount applicable items."

    "**PercentageDiscount**: '15OFF' -> 15% off.
    Capped by coupon.maxDiscount (e.g., max Rs 500)."

    "**BuyXGetYDiscount**: 'BUY2GET1' -> cheapest
    item free when buying 3 of same category."

    "**FreeShippingDiscount**: waives shipping fee."

    "**CashbackDiscount**: 10% back as store credit."

    "DiscountEngine maps DiscountType -> Strategy.
    Add TieredDiscount (10% on 1000, 20% on 2000)?
    One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

DiscountStrategy <|.. FlatAmountDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. PercentageDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. BuyXGetYDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. FreeShippingDiscount
DiscountStrategy <|.. CashbackDiscount
DiscountEngine --> DiscountStrategy : delegates >
DiscountEngine --> DiscountResult : returns >
CouponService --> DiscountEngine


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: CATEGORY-SPECIFIC DISCOUNT — Decorator Pattern
' ====================================================================
abstract class DiscountDecorator <<Decorator>> {
    # wrapped : DiscountStrategy
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class CategoryFilterDecorator {
    - applicableCategories : Set<ProductCategory>
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class BrandFilterDecorator {
    - applicableBrands : Set<String>
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

class MaxCapDecorator {
    - maxDiscount : double
    --
    + calculate(cart, coupon) : DiscountResult
}

note bottom of DiscountDecorator #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Layer discount rules.**
    "**Decorator Pattern** — layer conditions
    on top of base discount strategy."

    "'15% off on Electronics, max Rs 500':
    new MaxCapDecorator(500,
      new CategoryFilterDecorator(ELECTRONICS,
        new PercentageDiscount()))."

    "**CategoryFilterDecorator**: filters cart
    to only applicable items before calculating.
    **BrandFilterDecorator**: same for brands.
    **MaxCapDecorator**: caps the final discount."

    "Composable: stack any combination without
    modifying base strategies."
    **Pattern: Decorator | OCP, SRP**
end note

DiscountStrategy <|.. DiscountDecorator
DiscountDecorator o--> DiscountStrategy : wraps >
DiscountDecorator <|-- CategoryFilterDecorator
DiscountDecorator <|-- BrandFilterDecorator
DiscountDecorator <|-- MaxCapDecorator


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: BEST COUPON SUGGESTION
' ====================================================================
interface CouponRankingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + rank(coupons, cart) : List<Coupon>
}

class MaxSavingsRanking {
    - discountEngine : DiscountEngine
    --
    + rank(coupons, cart) : List<Coupon>
}

class PopularityRanking {
    --
    + rank(coupons, cart) : List<Coupon>
}

note bottom of CouponRankingStrategy #C8E6C9
    **STEP 7 - Suggest best coupon.**
    "getAvailableCoupons(cart): find all valid
    coupons for this cart. How to sort them?"

    "**Strategy Pattern:**
    **MaxSavingsRanking**: calculate discount for
    each coupon, sort by highest savings.
    Shows 'SAVE Rs 500 with FLAT500' first.
    **PopularityRanking**: sort by usage count."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

CouponRankingStrategy <|.. MaxSavingsRanking
CouponRankingStrategy <|.. PopularityRanking
CouponService --> CouponRankingStrategy : ranks with >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: OBSERVER — Notify on coupon events
' ====================================================================
interface CouponObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onCouponEvent(cart, coupon, event) : void
}

class UsageTrackingObserver {
    - couponRepository : CouponRepository
    --
    + onCouponEvent(cart, coupon, event) : void
}

class AnalyticsObserver {
    --
    + onCouponEvent(cart, coupon, event) : void
}

class PriceUpdateObserver {
    --
    + onCouponEvent(cart, coupon, event) : void
}

note bottom of CouponObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - React to coupon events.**
    "On applyCoupon / removeCoupon:"

    "**UsageTrackingObserver**: increments coupon's
    usage count (for limit enforcement).
    **AnalyticsObserver**: logs which coupons are
    used, conversion rate, avg discount.
    **PriceUpdateObserver**: recalculates cart
    total and updates the UI display."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

CouponObserver <|.. UsageTrackingObserver
CouponObserver <|.. AnalyticsObserver
CouponObserver <|.. PriceUpdateObserver


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Cart has Rs 2000 of items. User enters 'FLAT200'.
    CouponService looks up coupon -> **Chain of Responsibility**
    validates: active? not expired? cart >= minValue? usage limit OK?
    category match? -> All pass. **DiscountStrategy** (FlatAmountDiscount)
    calculates Rs 200 off. If category-specific, **Decorator** filters
    applicable items first. **MaxCapDecorator** ensures cap.
    Result: Rs 1800. Observer updates usage count + analytics."

    "6 patterns: **Facade**, **Chain of Responsibility** (validation),
    **Strategy** (x2: discount calculation + coupon ranking),
    **Decorator** (category/brand filter + max cap on discounts),
    **Observer** (usage tracking, analytics, price update).
    The Decorator on Strategy is the interview differentiator."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | User enters coupon code, calls CouponService.applyCoupon() | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Cart has items (Product + quantity), subtotal, category info | Composition | SRP |
    | 3 | Coupon: type, value, maxDiscount, minCart, categories, expiry, limits | Entity | Rich domain model |
    | 4 | Active? Expired? MinCart? UsageLimit? Category? Stackable? | Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP |
    | 5 | FlatAmount / Percentage / BuyXGetY / FreeShipping / Cashback | Strategy (discount) | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    | 6 | CategoryFilter + BrandFilter + MaxCap layered on strategy | Decorator | OCP, SRP |
    | 7 | Suggest best coupon: MaxSavings / Popularity ranking | Strategy (ranking) | OCP |
    | 8 | Usage tracking, analytics, price update on apply/remove | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Validate** = Step 4 (chain) | **Calculate** = Steps 5-6 (strategy + decorator) | **Suggest** = Step 7 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
